               <msContents>
                  <summary>Dersana Mika'el, containing an extraordinary number of names of owners/ donars. Miniatures are added later over the top of text. F<locus target="#22v">fols. 22v, </locus> and 45r mention an owner, ወለተ ገብርኤል, and ወልደ አቢየ እግዚአ (the name suggests an origin in Tigray). F<locus target="#24r">24r, </locus> and 83r mention ገብረ ኪዳን. F<locus target="#37r">37r, </locus>, 43v, and 81r mention ወለተ ሥላሴ. F<locus target="#38r">38r, </locus> and 81r mention ገብረ ማርያም. <locus target="#67v">67v, </locus> mentions ገብረ ኢየሱስ. <locus target="#69r">69r, </locus> mentions ስብለ ወንጌል. F<locus target="#75v">75v, </locus> and 78v and passim mention ገብረ ሚካኤል. F<locus target="#78v">78v, </locus> and 101v mention ወለተ ኪዳን. <locus target="#83r">83r, </locus> mentions ወለተ ማርያም. <locus target="#93v">93v, </locus> mentions ሰይፈ ያሬድ. <locus target="#101v">101v, </locus> mentions ገብረ ሕይዎት. <locus target="#106v">106v, </locus> mentions ተክለ ዮሐንስ. <locus target="#124r">124r, </locus> mentions ወለተ ገብርኤል and ኃይለ ማርያም. F<locus target="#121r">121r, </locus> and 124r mention the scribe, ፍሥሐ ጽዮን. On <locus target="#116r">116r, </locus> and passim, a secondary owner has writtin in red ink pen the name ገብረ ተክለ ሀያማኖት. <locus target="#127r">127r, </locus> and <locus target="#128v">128v, </locus> contain a varia, an excerpt from Chants called Ziq, written in a different hand. F<locus target="#127v">127v</locus>-128r probably also contained text from Ziq, but miniatures now cover the text.</summary>
